\series default
 (or dot product) between vectors of the same size.
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{a}=\mathbf{Ia=}\begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 1 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}\cdot\begin{bmatrix}a_{1}\\
a_{2}\\
a_{3}
\end{bmatrix}=\mathbf{aI}=\begin{bmatrix}a_{1} & a_{2} & a_{3}\end{bmatrix}\cdot\begin{bmatrix}1 & 0 & 0\\
0 & 1 & 0\\
0 & 0 & 1
\end{bmatrix}=\begin{bmatrix}a_{1}\\
a_{2}\\
a_{3}
\end{bmatrix}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size small
The rule for multiplication is straightforward: it is a 
\series bold
row-by-column
\series default
