\begin_layout Itemize

\size footnotesize
Is there such a thing like the inverse of a matrix? YES!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\size footnotesize
The solution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{Ax}=\mathbf{c}$
\end_inset

 is the matrix 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{B}$
\end_inset

 that satisfies 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{x}=\mathbf{Bc}$
\end_inset

, and this is the inverse of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A}$
\end_inset

.
 
