\begin_layout Definition

\size footnotesize
The inverse of a matrix must satisfy the relationship 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{BA}=\mathbf{I}$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the product of a matrix by its inverse is equal to the identity matrix:
 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbf{A^{-1}A}=\mathbf{I}$
